OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,364,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F363A1782236890
OL,3,CWoman, 72, guilty of murdering husband
OL,4,Cafter claiming he 'fell on knife'
OL,6,FHer account was initially accepted,
OL,7,Fbut she was arrested five days later
OL,8,Fwhen concerns were raised following a
OL,9,Fpost-mortem examination.
OL,11,FIn her police interview, she said Mr
OL,12,FBerman had carried her tray with a
OL,13,Fplate, cup and knife into the kitchen.
OL,15,FShe claimed to have heard a sound,
OL,16,Flike he had fallen, and then he said,
OL,17,F"It's OK I slipped". She said she then
OL,18,Fheard a groan and ran into the kitchen
OL,19,Fwhere she discovered him lying face
OL,20,Fdown.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,364,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F363A1782236890
OL,3,CWoman, 72, guilty of murdering husband
OL,4,Cafter claiming he 'fell on knife'
OL,6,FBut pathologists concluded the chest
OL,7,Fwound was not an accident but was due
OL,8,Fto an inflicted injury, Manchester
OL,9,FMinshull Street Crown Court heard.
OL,11,FMr Berman also had a stab wound to his
OL,12,Fright middle finger which prosecutors
OL,13,Fsaid was a common self-defensive
OL,14,Finjury.
OL,16,FConcerns were also raised about her
OL,17,Fbehaviour at the scene, where she told
OL,18,Fpolice on th driveway of her home and
OL,19,Fshe said: "You don't think I murdered
OL,20,Fhim do you?"
OL,26,@{D@KOU|D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,364,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F363A1782236890
OL,3,CWoman, 72, guilty of murdering husband
OL,4,Cafter claiming he 'fell on knife'
OL,6,FInvestigators noted she appeared "very
OL,7,Fcalm and matter of fact", and had very
OL,8,Flittle blood on her clothing despite
OL,9,Fclaiming she had rolled her husband
OL,10,Fover after finding him injured.
OL,12,FAnalysis of her mobile phone also
OL,13,Frevealed it had been unlocked 25
OL,14,Fseconds before the emergency call was
OL,15,Fmade.
OL,17,FThe court also heard that despite
OL,18,Freceiving instructions from the call
OL,19,Fhandler, Mrs Berman did not begin CPR
OL,20,Funtil more than six minutes into the
OL,21,Fcall.
OL,26,@nD@bOUoD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,364,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F363A1782236890
OL,3,CWoman, 72, guilty of murdering husband
OL,4,Cafter claiming he 'fell on knife'
OL,6,FDuring that time there were periods of
OL,7,Fsilence, and she answered another
OL,8,Ftelephone in the same room.
OL,10,FA retrial was ordered after a previous
OL,11,Fjury was discharged in December when
OL,12,Fthey could not reach a verdict over
OL,13,Fthe allegation.
OL,15,FPathologists later ruled out the
OL,16,Fpossibility of an accidental injury
OL,17,Fand concluded the wound had been
OL,18,Fdeliberately inflicted.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,364,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F363A1782236890
OL,3,CWoman, 72, guilty of murdering husband
OL,4,Cafter claiming he 'fell on knife'
OL,6,FSazeeda Ismail, of the Crown
OL,7,FProsecution Service, said: "Daryl
OL,8,FBerman stabbed her husband of 27 years
OL,9,Fin the chest and intentionally caused
OL,10,Fhis death.
OL,12,F"She lied to paramedics, police and
OL,13,Ffamily members when she claimed Mr
OL,14,FBerman had accidentally sustained his
OL,15,Ffatal injuries.
OL,17,F"The jury saw through her lies and
OL,18,Fconvicted her of murder, due to the
OL,19,Fstrength of the prosecution's case.
OL,26,@oD@\OUtD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
